claim.claim-text:
1. A computer-implemented method comprising:
under control of one or more computer systems configured with executable instructions,
receiving a first order for one or more first items, wherein the first order is associated with an account and has one or more first order attributes;
after receiving the first order and before the first order is completed, receiving a phrase token and a selection of one or more second items for a second potential order that has one or more second order attributes;
associating the phrase token with the account;
determining that consolidation of the first order and the second potential order is available because the first order is not completed;
determining that at least one first order attribute is different than at least one second order attribute and that consolidation of the first order and the second potential order is available if the at least one first order attribute or the at least one second order attribute is modified so that the at least one first order attribute and the at least one second order attribute match;
receiving an indication to modify the at least one first order attribute or the at least one second order attribute so the at least one first order attribute or the at least one second order attribute match; and
predicting a consolidated cost associated with fulfillment of the first order and the second potential order when the first order and the second potential order are consolidated.

9. One or more non-transitory computer-readable storage media storing computer-executable instructions that, when executed, cause one or more processors to perform acts comprising:
receiving, as part of a potential order, a selection of one or more items from a user, wherein the potential order includes one or more potential order attributes;
determining that a previous order is available for consolidation, wherein the previous order is an open order that includes one or more previous items selected by the user and one or more previous order attributes;
determining that at least one potential order attribute is different than at least one previous order attribute and that consolidation of the potential order and the previous order into a single order is available if the at least one potential order attribute or the at least one previous order attribute is modified;
calculating a cost differential between processing the single order and processing separate orders that includes non-consolidation of the previous order and the potential order; and
modifying, based on the cost differential indicating that processing the single order is less expensive than processing the separate orders, the at least one potential order attribute or the at least one previous order attribute so that the single order can be processed.

18. A system comprising:
one or more processors;
one or more memories;
a first module, stored in the one or more memories and executable on the one or more processors, that determines if consolidation of a current order and a previously placed order is available, wherein consolidation is available before the previously placed order is completed;
a second module, stored in the one or more memories and executable on the one or more processors, that determines that an attribute of the current order does not match a corresponding attribute of the previously placed order and that modifies the attribute of the current order or the corresponding attribute of the previously placed order so the attribute of the current order and the corresponding attribute of the previously placed order match or are of a same type; and
a third module, stored in the one or memories and executable on the one or more processors, that predicts a cost savings resulting from consolidating the current order and the previously placed order, and that serves the cost savings for presentation to the user.

19. The system of claim 18, wherein the third module predicts the cost savings by:
calculating a cost for the current order;
calculating a cost for the previously placed order;
calculating a cost of a consolidated order comprising the current order and the previously placed order; and
determining a difference between: (i) the cost for the current order and the cost for the previously placed order, and (ii) the cost of the consolidated order comprising the current order and the previously placed order.

21. A method comprising:
receiving a first order placed by a user, the first order including one or more first order attributes;
after receiving the first order and while the first order is open and not yet completed, receiving a selection of one or more items that are part of a second potential order that includes one or more second order attributes;
determining, at one or more servers, that at least one first order attribute is different than at least one second order attribute and that consolidation of the first order and the second potential order is available if the at least one first order attribute or the at least one second order attribute is modified so that the at least one first order attribute and the at least one second order attribute match;
providing, to a user device associated with the user, an indication;
to modify the at least one first order attribute or the at least one second order attribute so that the at least one first order attribute and the at least one second order attribute match;
receiving an instruction to modify the at least one first order attribute or the at least one second order attribute so that the at least one first order attribute and the at least one second order attribute match; and
in response to receiving the instruction, placing a consolidated order that includes items of the first order and the one or more items that are part of the second potential order.
